Kremlin Council Says Magnitsky Case Falsified, Vedomosti Says

-- B y   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 
2011-04-26T04:15:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/kremlin-council-says-magnitsky-case-falsified-vedomosti-says.html
Russian President  Dmitry Medvedev ’s
human rights council found that tax evasion charges against
Sergei Magnitsky, a lawyer representing Hermitage Capital
Management, were fabricated, Vedomosti  reported .  The charges brought against Magnitsky, who died in pretrial
detention in 2009, were fabricated by officials from the
Interior Ministry and the Federal Security Service, the
newspaper reported, citing a copy of the council’s preliminary
findings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Rose in Moscow at 
 rrose10@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net . 